Here are lot's of work needed to do for the data visulization. I know this visualization project. Therefore, most of the data wragling process skipped here but some important steps of wrangle I putted here. Important steps of wrangling after wrangling analysis following:

  1. Many district have been missplled. Also, so many times they putted small village name, direction (east, west, north, south) instead of district name.
  2. district there are also subdistrict which I combined into one. For instance, JAIPUR EAST, WEST, NORTH, SOUTH = JAIPUR. Those are unnecessary divided into region. However, some of are legally district by this kind of name. For example, SOUTH DELHI, EAST DELHI etc.
  3. Most important thing in district column in this dataset, they had putted G.R.P. stands for Government Railway Police in district. So, it's very difficult to get appropritate district name. Thus, insteading of deleting those rows I keep them as statename_GRP(ASSAM_GRP). It is not district but do help us evaluate the other things that's why keep them.
  4. Some of the data had irrelevant like SPL CELL, STF in the district..... I writed down in below.

def annotation_perc(ax, perc_list):
    i = 0

        plt.annotate('{:.0f}\n{:.2f}%'.format(p.get_height(), perc_list[i]),
                   (p.get_x()+p.get_width()/2, p.get_height()),
                   color = 'black', va='bottom', ha='center', size=10)
        i+=1

IPC crimes against women:¶

  1. rape: Rape is a type of sexual assault usually involving sexual intercourse against a person without that person's consent.
  2. dowry death: Dowry deaths are deaths of married women who are murdered or driven to suicide by continuous harassment and torture by their husbands
  3. assault_on_women_with_intent_to_outrage_her_modesty: Assault on women because she belongs to the lower class background and lower cast in the society.
  4. insult_to_modesty_of_women: Insult to the women because she belongs to the lower class and lower cast background in the society.
  5. cruelty_by_husband_or_his_relatives: Physically and Mentally reprimand to the women after marriage by her husbend and relative.

def aggregate_crimes(x, y):
    data = india_crimes.groupby(x)[y].sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(ascending = True, by= y).reset_index(drop=True)
    return data

In [119]:
def concatenate_loop_dfs(df_temp, df_full, axis=0):
    """
    to avoid retyping the same line of code for every df.
    the parameters should be the temporary df created at each loop and the concatenated DF that will contain all
    values which must first be initialized (outside the loop) as df_name = pd.DataFrame(). """ 
    if df_full.empty:
    	df_full = df_temp
    else:
    	df_full = pd.concat([df_full, df_temp], axis=axis)
    return df_full
In [120]:
df_final = pd.DataFrame()
In [121]:
for yr in year_lst:
    # The query function does a search for where
    # the @year means the external variable, in this case the input from loop
    # then you'll have a temporary DF with only the year and sorting and getting top3
    df2 = india_crimes.query("year == @yr")

    df_temp = df2.groupby(['year','states_or_union_territories']).size()
    df_temp = df_temp[df_temp!=0].sort_values(ascending = False).head(3).reset_index(name='count')
    # finally you'll call our function that will keep concating the tmp DFs
    df_final = concatenate_loop_dfs(df_temp, df_final)
